Note:
Runa Standard Library: Advanced Property-Based Testing Framework

Production-grade property testing system designed to surpass competitors like
Hypothesis, QuickCheck, PropEr, and ScalaCheck. Comprehensive property-based
testing with intelligent test case generation and shrinking capabilities.

Key Features:
- Comprehensive generators for primitive and complex data types
- Advanced test case shrinking with minimal counterexample finding
- Property composition and combination strategies
- Stateful property testing with model-based verification
- Custom data generators with constraints and dependencies
- Integrated shrinking strategies for faster debugging
- Statistical analysis of test case distributions
- Regression testing with deterministic replay capabilities
- Performance property testing with resource constraints
- Property-based mutation testing integration
- Automatic invariant discovery and verification
- Integration with existing test frameworks and CI systems

Architecture:
Built on Runa's natural language primitives with optimized generation
and shrinking algorithms. Provides both high-level property specification
APIs and low-level generator customization capabilities.
:End Note

Import "collections" as Collections
Import "string/format" as Format
Import "testing/unittest" as UnitTest

Note: Core Property Testing Types and Structures
Type called "PropertyTest":
    property_name as String
    property_description as String
    property_function as String
    generators as List[Generator]
    preconditions as List[String]
    postconditions as List[String]
    invariants as List[String]
    max_examples as Integer
    max_shrinks as Integer
    seed as Optional[Integer]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "Generator":
    generator_name as String
    data_type as String
    generation_strategy as GenerationStrategy
    constraints as List[Constraint]
    dependency_generators as List[String]
    distribution_weights as Dictionary[String, Float]
    generated_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type GenerationStrategy is:
    | RandomGeneration
    | ExhaustiveGeneration
    | ConstraintBasedGeneration
    | ModelBasedGeneration
    | CompositeGeneration with sub_generators as List[Generator]

Type called "Constraint":
    constraint_type as String
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    validation_function as Optional[String]
    error_message as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "GeneratedValue":
    value as Any
    generator_path as List[String]
    generation_metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    shrink_history as List[Any]
    complexity_score as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PropertyTestResult":
    property_name as String
    test_passed as Boolean
    examples_tested as Integer
    counterexample as Optional[Counterexample]
    shrink_attempts as Integer
    execution_time as Float
    distribution_analysis as DistributionAnalysis
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "Counterexample":
    failing_input as GeneratedValue
    property_violation as String
    original_input as GeneratedValue
    shrink_path as List[GeneratedValue]
    minimal_example as Boolean
    reproduction_seed as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DistributionAnalysis":
    generated_types as Dictionary[String, Integer]
    value_ranges as Dictionary[String, ValueRange]
    distribution_quality as Float
    coverage_statistics as Dictionary[String, Float]
    bias_detection as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ValueRange":
    min_value as Any
    max_value as Any
    median_value as Any
    distribution_type as String
    sample_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PropertyRunner":
    registered_properties as Dictionary[String, PropertyTest]
    default_generators as Dictionary[String, Generator]
    shrinking_strategies as Dictionary[String, ShrinkingStrategy]
    execution_statistics as PropertyExecutionStats
    configuration as PropertyTestConfiguration
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ShrinkingStrategy":
    strategy_name as String
    applicable_types as List[String]
    shrink_function as String
    effectiveness_score as Float
    application_count as Integer
    successful_shrinks as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PropertyExecutionStats":
    total_properties_run as Integer
    properties_passed as Integer
    properties_failed as Integer
    total_examples_generated as Integer
    total_shrink_attempts as Integer
    average_shrink_time as Float
    counterexamples_found as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PropertyTestConfiguration":
    default_max_examples as Integer
    default_max_shrinks as Integer
    enable_distribution_analysis as Boolean
    enable_shrinking as Boolean
    shrinking_timeout as Float
    parallel_execution as Boolean
    deterministic_mode as Boolean
    verbosity_level as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Property Test Creation and Registration
Process called "create_property_test" that takes name as String and property_function as String returns PropertyTest:
    Note: Create basic property test with default configuration
    Return PropertyTest with:
    property_name as name
    property_description as ""
    property_function as property_function
    generators as list containing
    preconditions as list containing
    postconditions as list containing
    invariants as list containing
    max_examples as 100
    max_shrinks as 100
    seed as None
    metadata as dictionary containing "created_at" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "create_property_test_with_generators" that takes name as String and property_function as String and generators as List[Generator] returns PropertyTest:
    Note: Create property test with specified generators
    Let property be create_property_test with name as name and property_function as property_function
    Set property.generators to generators
    Set property.metadata at key "custom_generators" to length of generators
    Return property

Process called "add_precondition" that takes property as PropertyTest and condition_function as String returns PropertyTest:
    Note: Add precondition that must be true before property evaluation
    Add condition_function to property.preconditions
    Set property.metadata at key "preconditions_count" to length of property.preconditions
    Return property

Process called "add_postcondition" that takes property as PropertyTest and condition_function as String returns PropertyTest:
    Note: Add postcondition that must be true after property evaluation
    Add condition_function to property.postconditions
    Set property.metadata at key "postconditions_count" to length of property.postconditions
    Return property

Process called "add_invariant" that takes property as PropertyTest and invariant_function as String returns PropertyTest:
    Note: Add invariant that must hold throughout property execution
    Add invariant_function to property.invariants
    Set property.metadata at key "invariants_count" to length of property.invariants
    Return property

Process called "create_property_runner" returns PropertyRunner:
    Note: Create property runner with default configuration
    Let config be PropertyTestConfiguration with:
    default_max_examples as 100
    default_max_shrinks as 100
    enable_distribution_analysis as true
    enable_shrinking as true
    shrinking_timeout as 30.0
    parallel_execution as false
    deterministic_mode as false
    verbosity_level as 1
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Let stats be PropertyExecutionStats with:
    total_properties_run as 0
    properties_passed as 0
    properties_failed as 0
    total_examples_generated as 0
    total_shrink_attempts as 0
    average_shrink_time as 0.0
    counterexamples_found as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Return PropertyRunner with:
    registered_properties as dictionary containing
    default_generators as create_default_generators
    shrinking_strategies as create_default_shrinking_strategies
    execution_statistics as stats
    configuration as config
    metadata as dictionary containing "created_at" as get_current_timestamp

Note: Core Generator Creation and Management
Process called "create_integer_generator" that takes min_value as Integer and max_value as Integer returns Generator:
    Note: Create generator for integers within specified range
    Let range_constraint be Constraint with:
    constraint_type as "range"
    parameters as dictionary containing "min" as min_value, "max" as max_value
    validation_function as None
    error_message as "Value must be between " Format.integer_to_string with value as min_value " and " Format.integer_to_string with value as max_value
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Return Generator with:
    generator_name as "integer_generator"
    data_type as "integer"
    generation_strategy as RandomGeneration
    constraints as list containing range_constraint
    dependency_generators as list containing
    distribution_weights as dictionary containing
    generated_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing "min_value" as min_value, "max_value" as max_value

Process called "create_string_generator" that takes min_length as Integer and max_length as Integer returns Generator:
    Note: Create generator for strings within specified length range
    Let length_constraint be Constraint with:
    constraint_type as "length"
    parameters as dictionary containing "min_length" as min_length, "max_length" as max_length
    validation_function as None
    error_message as "String length must be between " Format.integer_to_string with value as min_length " and " Format.integer_to_string with value as max_length
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Return Generator with:
    generator_name as "string_generator"
    data_type as "string"
    generation_strategy as RandomGeneration
    constraints as list containing length_constraint
    dependency_generators as list containing
    distribution_weights as dictionary containing
    generated_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing "min_length" as min_length, "max_length" as max_length

Process called "create_list_generator" that takes element_generator as Generator and min_size as Integer and max_size as Integer returns Generator:
    Note: Create generator for lists with specified element generator and size constraints
    Let size_constraint be Constraint with:
    constraint_type as "size"
    parameters as dictionary containing "min_size" as min_size, "max_size" as max_size
    validation_function as None
    error_message as "List size must be between " Format.integer_to_string with value as min_size " and " Format.integer_to_string with value as max_size
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Return Generator with:
    generator_name as "list_generator"
    data_type as "list"
    generation_strategy as CompositeGeneration with sub_generators as list containing element_generator
    constraints as list containing size_constraint
    dependency_generators as list containing element_generator.generator_name
    distribution_weights as dictionary containing
    generated_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing "element_type" as element_generator.data_type

Process called "create_dictionary_generator" that takes key_generator as Generator and value_generator as Generator and min_size as Integer and max_size as Integer returns Generator:
    Note: Create generator for dictionaries with specified key/value generators
    Let size_constraint be Constraint with:
    constraint_type as "size"
    parameters as dictionary containing "min_size" as min_size, "max_size" as max_size
    validation_function as None
    error_message as "Dictionary size must be between " Format.integer_to_string with value as min_size " and " Format.integer_to_string with value as max_size
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Return Generator with:
    generator_name as "dictionary_generator"
    data_type as "dictionary"
    generation_strategy as CompositeGeneration with sub_generators as list containing key_generator, value_generator
    constraints as list containing size_constraint
    dependency_generators as list containing key_generator.generator_name, value_generator.generator_name
    distribution_weights as dictionary containing
    generated_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing "key_type" as key_generator.data_type, "value_type" as value_generator.data_type

Process called "create_choice_generator" that takes choices as List[Any] returns Generator:
    Note: Create generator that selects from predefined choices
    Let choices_constraint be Constraint with:
    constraint_type as "choices"
    parameters as dictionary containing "valid_choices" as choices
    validation_function as None
    error_message as "Value must be one of the predefined choices"
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Return Generator with:
    generator_name as "choice_generator"
    data_type as "choice"
    generation_strategy as RandomGeneration
    constraints as list containing choices_constraint
    dependency_generators as list containing
    distribution_weights as create_uniform_distribution with choices as choices
    generated_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing "choices_count" as length of choices

Note: Property Test Execution Engine
Process called "run_property_test" that takes runner as PropertyRunner and property as PropertyTest returns PropertyTestResult:
    Note: Execute property test with comprehensive generation and verification
    Let test_start_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let examples_tested be 0
    Let counterexample_found be None
    Let shrink_attempts be 0 Set runner.execution_statistics.total_properties_run to runner.execution_statistics.total_properties_run + 1 Note: Initialize distribution analysis tracking
    Let distribution_tracker be initialize_distribution_analysis with property as property Note: Determine number of examples to generate
    Let max_examples be if property.max_examples is greater than 0 then property.max_examples else runner.configuration.default_max_examples Note: Set deterministic seed if specified
    If property.seed is not None:
    Set random_seed to property.seed While examples_tested is less than max_examples and counterexample_found is None:
    Note: Generate test inputs using property generators
    Let generated_inputs be generate_test_inputs with property as property and runner as runner Set runner.execution_statistics.total_examples_generated to runner.execution_statistics.total_examples_generated + 1 Note: Update distribution analysis
    Update distribution_tracker with inputs as generated_inputs Note: Check preconditions
    If not check_preconditions with property as property and inputs as generated_inputs:
    Continue Note: Execute property function
    Let property_result be execute_property_function with property as property and inputs as generated_inputs If not property_result.success:
    Note: Property violation found - create counterexample
    Set counterexample_found to Some with value as create_counterexample with property as property and inputs as generated_inputs and result as property_result Note: Attempt to shrink counterexample if enabled
    If runner.configuration.enable_shrinking:
    Let shrink_result be shrink_counterexample with runner as runner and counterexample as counterexample_found and property as property
    Set counterexample_found to shrink_result.shrunk_counterexample
    Set shrink_attempts to shrink_result.attempts
    Set runner.execution_statistics.total_shrink_attempts to runner.execution_statistics.total_shrink_attempts + shrink_attempts Set runner.execution_statistics.counterexamples_found to runner.execution_statistics.counterexamples_found + 1 Note: Check postconditions and invariants if property passed
    If property_result.success:
    If not check_postconditions with property as property and inputs as generated_inputs and result as property_result:
    Set counterexample_found to Some with value as create_postcondition_violation with property as property and inputs as generated_inputs and result as property_result Set examples_tested to examples_tested + 1 Let test_end_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let test_passed be counterexample_found is None Note: Update runner statistics
    If test_passed:
    Set runner.execution_statistics.properties_passed to runner.execution_statistics.properties_passed + 1
    Otherwise:
    Set runner.execution_statistics.properties_failed to runner.execution_statistics.properties_failed + 1 Note: Finalize distribution analysis
    Let distribution_analysis be finalize_distribution_analysis with tracker as distribution_tracker Return PropertyTestResult with:
    property_name as property.property_name
    test_passed as test_passed
    examples_tested as examples_tested
    counterexample as counterexample_found
    shrink_attempts as shrink_attempts
    execution_time as test_end_time - test_start_time
    distribution_analysis as distribution_analysis
    metadata as dictionary containing "test_completed_at" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "generate_test_inputs" that takes property as PropertyTest and runner as PropertyRunner returns List[GeneratedValue]:
    Note: Generate test inputs for property using configured generators
    Let generated_inputs be list containing For each generator in property.generators:
    Let generated_value be generate_value_with_generator with generator as generator and runner as runner
    Add generated_value to generated_inputs Note: If no generators specified, try to infer from property function signature
    If length of generated_inputs is equal to 0:
    Let inferred_generators be infer_generators_from_function with property as property and runner as runner
    For each generator in inferred_generators:
    Let generated_value be generate_value_with_generator with generator as generator and runner as runner
    Add generated_value to generated_inputs Return generated_inputs

Process called "generate_value_with_generator" that takes generator as Generator and runner as PropertyRunner returns GeneratedValue:
    Note: Generate single value using specified generator
    Set generator.generated_count to generator.generated_count + 1 Let generated_data be execute_generation_strategy with generator as generator and runner as runner
    Let complexity_score be calculate_complexity_score with value as generated_data and generator as generator Return GeneratedValue with:
    value as generated_data
    generator_path as list containing generator.generator_name
    generation_metadata as create_generation_metadata with generator as generator
    shrink_history as list containing
    complexity_score as complexity_score
    metadata as dictionary containing "generated_at" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "execute_generation_strategy" that takes generator as Generator and runner as PropertyRunner returns Any:
    Note: Execute specific generation strategy to produce data
    Match generator.generation_strategy:
    When RandomGeneration:
    Return generate_random_value with generator as generator
    When ExhaustiveGeneration:
    Return generate_exhaustive_value with generator as generator
    When ConstraintBasedGeneration:
    Return generate_constraint_based_value with generator as generator
    When ModelBasedGeneration:
    Return generate_model_based_value with generator as generator
    When CompositeGeneration with sub_generators as sub_gens:
    Return generate_composite_value with generator as generator and sub_generators as sub_gens and runner as runner
    Otherwise:
    Return generate_random_value with generator as generator

Process called "generate_random_value" that takes generator as Generator returns Any:
    Note: Generate random value based on generator type and constraints
    Match generator.data_type:
    When "integer":
    Let min_val be get_constraint_parameter with generator as generator and constraint_type as "range" and parameter as "min" and default as -1000
    Let max_val be get_constraint_parameter with generator as generator and constraint_type as "range" and parameter as "max" and default as 1000
    Return generate_random_integer with min as min_val and max as max_val When "string":
    Let min_len be get_constraint_parameter with generator as generator and constraint_type as "length" and parameter as "min_length" and default as 0
    Let max_len be get_constraint_parameter with generator as generator and constraint_type as "length" and parameter as "max_length" and default as 20
    Let length be generate_random_integer with min as min_len and max as max_len
    Return generate_random_string with length as length When "choice":
    Let choices be get_constraint_parameter with generator as generator and constraint_type as "choices" and parameter as "valid_choices" and default as list containing "default"
    Let index be generate_random_integer with min as 0 and max as (length of choices - 1)
    Return choices[index] When "boolean":
    Let random_value be generate_random_integer with min as 0 and max as 1
    Return random_value is equal to 1 Otherwise:
    Return generate_default_random_value with generator as generator

Process called "generate_composite_value" that takes generator as Generator and sub_generators as List[Generator] and runner as PropertyRunner returns Any:
    Note: Generate composite value using sub-generators
    Match generator.data_type:
    When "list":
    Let min_size be get_constraint_parameter with generator as generator and constraint_type as "size" and parameter as "min_size" and default as 0
    Let max_size be get_constraint_parameter with generator as generator and constraint_type as "size" and parameter as "max_size" and default as 10
    Let list_size be generate_random_integer with min as min_size and max as max_size
    Let element_generator be sub_generators[0] Let generated_list be list containing
    For i from 1 to list_size:
    Let element_value be generate_value_with_generator with generator as element_generator and runner as runner
    Add element_value.value to generated_list Return generated_list When "dictionary":
    Let min_size be get_constraint_parameter with generator as generator and constraint_type as "size" and parameter as "min_size" and default as 0
    Let max_size be get_constraint_parameter with generator as generator and constraint_type as "size" and parameter as "max_size" and default as 10
    Let dict_size be generate_random_integer with min as min_size and max as max_size
    Let key_generator be sub_generators[0]
    Let value_generator be sub_generators[1] Let generated_dict be dictionary containing
    For i from 1 to dict_size:
    Let key_value be generate_value_with_generator with generator as key_generator and runner as runner
    Let val_value be generate_value_with_generator with generator as value_generator and runner as runner
    Set generated_dict at key Format.convert_to_string with value as key_value.value to val_value.value Return generated_dict Otherwise:
    Return dictionary containing "error" as "Unknown composite type"

Note: Property Function Execution and Validation
Process called "execute_property_function" that takes property as PropertyTest and inputs as List[GeneratedValue] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute property function with generated inputs
    Try:
    Note: Prepare function arguments from generated values
    Let function_args be list containing
    For each input in inputs:
    Add input.value to function_args Note: Execute property function
    Let property_result be call_property_function with function_name as property.property_function and args as function_args If property_result.success and property_result.result:
    Return dictionary containing:
    "success" as true,
    "result" as property_result.result,
    "output" as property_result.output,
    "execution_time" as property_result.execution_time,
    "error" as ""
    Otherwise:
    Return dictionary containing:
    "success" as false,
    "result" as false,
    "output" as property_result.output,
    "execution_time" as property_result.execution_time,
    "error" as property_result.error_message Catch error:
    Return dictionary containing:
    "success" as false,
    "result" as false,
    "output" as "",
    "execution_time" as 0.0,
    "error" as error.message

Process called "check_preconditions" that takes property as PropertyTest and inputs as List[GeneratedValue] returns Boolean:
    Note: Check all preconditions before property execution
    If length of property.preconditions is equal to 0:
    Return true For each precondition_func in property.preconditions:
    Let function_args be list containing
    For each input in inputs:
    Add input.value to function_args Let precondition_result be call_property_function with function_name as precondition_func and args as function_args
    If not precondition_result.success or not precondition_result.result:
    Return false Return true

Process called "check_postconditions" that takes property as PropertyTest and inputs as List[GeneratedValue] and result as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Note: Check all postconditions after property execution
    If length of property.postconditions is equal to 0:
    Return true For each postcondition_func in property.postconditions:
    Let function_args be list containing
    For each input in inputs:
    Add input.value to function_args
    Add result to function_args Let postcondition_result be call_property_function with function_name as postcondition_func and args as function_args
    If not postcondition_result.success or not postcondition_result.result:
    Return false Return true

Note: Counterexample Creation and Shrinking
Process called "create_counterexample" that takes property as PropertyTest and inputs as List[GeneratedValue] and result as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Counterexample:
    Note: Create counterexample from failing property execution
    Return Counterexample with:
    failing_input as inputs[0]
    property_violation as result["error"]
    original_input as inputs[0]
    shrink_path as list containing
    minimal_example as false
    reproduction_seed as get_current_timestamp mod 1000000
    metadata as dictionary containing "violation_type" as "property_failure", "created_at" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "shrink_counterexample" that takes runner as PropertyRunner and counterexample as Counterexample and property as PropertyTest returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Attempt to shrink counterexample to minimal failing case
    Let shrink_start_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let current_counterexample be counterexample
    Let shrink_attempts be 0
    Let max_shrinks be property.max_shrinks While shrink_attempts is less than max_shrinks and get_current_timestamp - shrink_start_time is less than runner.configuration.shrinking_timeout:
    Let shrink_candidate be attempt_shrink with runner as runner and counterexample as current_counterexample and property as property If shrink_candidate is not None:
    Note: Test if shrunken candidate still fails the property
    Let shrink_test_result be test_counterexample_validity with candidate as shrink_candidate and property as property If not shrink_test_result.property_passes:
    Set current_counterexample to shrink_candidate
    Add shrink_candidate.failing_input to current_counterexample.shrink_path
    Set current_counterexample.minimal_example to true
    Set runner.shrinking_strategies["default"].successful_shrinks to runner.shrinking_strategies["default"].successful_shrinks + 1 Set shrink_attempts to shrink_attempts + 1
    Set runner.shrinking_strategies["default"].application_count to runner.shrinking_strategies["default"].application_count + 1 Let shrink_time be get_current_timestamp - shrink_start_time
    Set runner.execution_statistics.average_shrink_time to (runner.execution_statistics.average_shrink_time + shrink_time) divided by 2.0 Return dictionary containing:
    "shrunk_counterexample" as current_counterexample,
    "attempts" as shrink_attempts,
    "shrink_time" as shrink_time

Process called "attempt_shrink" that takes runner as PropertyRunner and counterexample as Counterexample and property as PropertyTest returns Optional[Counterexample]:
    Note: Attempt to shrink counterexample using available strategies
    Let input_value be counterexample.failing_input.value
    Let shrinking_strategy be select_shrinking_strategy with runner as runner and value_type as get_value_type with value as input_value If shrinking_strategy is not None:
    Let shrunk_value be apply_shrinking_strategy with strategy as shrinking_strategy and value as input_value
    If shrunk_value is not None and not values_are_equal with actual as shrunk_value and expected as input_value:
    Let shrunk_generated_value be GeneratedValue with:
    value as shrunk_value
    generator_path as counterexample.failing_input.generator_path
    generation_metadata as counterexample.failing_input.generation_metadata
    shrink_history as counterexample.failing_input.shrink_history
    complexity_score as calculate_complexity_score with value as shrunk_value and generator as None
    metadata as dictionary containing "shrunk_from" as input_value Add input_value to shrunk_generated_value.shrink_history Return Some with value as Counterexample with:
    failing_input as shrunk_generated_value
    property_violation as counterexample.property_violation
    original_input as counterexample.original_input
    shrink_path as counterexample.shrink_path
    minimal_example as false
    reproduction_seed as counterexample.reproduction_seed
    metadata as dictionary containing "shrink_attempt" as get_current_timestamp Return None

Note: Shrinking Strategies Implementation
Process called "apply_shrinking_strategy" that takes strategy as ShrinkingStrategy and value as Any returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Apply specific shrinking strategy to value
    Match strategy.strategy_name:
    When "integer_shrink":
    Return shrink_integer_value with value as value
    When "string_shrink":
    Return shrink_string_value with value as value
    When "list_shrink":
    Return shrink_list_value with value as value
    When "dictionary_shrink":
    Return shrink_dictionary_value with value as value
    Otherwise:
    Return None

Process called "shrink_integer_value" that takes value as Any returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Shrink integer towards zero
    If value is Integer:
    If value is greater than 0:
    Let shrunk_value be value divided by 2
    Return Some with value as shrunk_value
    Otherwise if value is less than 0:
    Let shrunk_value be value divided by 2
    Return Some with value as shrunk_value Return None

Process called "shrink_string_value" that takes value as Any returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Shrink string by reducing length
    If value is String and length of value is greater than 0:
    Let new_length be length of value divided by 2
    If new_length is less than 1:
    Set new_length to 0
    Let shrunk_string be Format.substring with s as value and start as 0 and end as new_length
    Return Some with value as shrunk_string Return None

Process called "shrink_list_value" that takes value as Any returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Shrink list by removing elements
    If value is List and length of value is greater than 0:
    Let new_size be length of value divided by 2
    If new_size is less than 1:
    Return Some with value as list containing Let shrunk_list be list containing
    For i from 0 to (new_size - 1):
    Add value[i] to shrunk_list Return Some with value as shrunk_list Return None

Process called "shrink_dictionary_value" that takes value as Any returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Shrink dictionary by removing key-value pairs
    If value is Dictionary:
    Let keys_list be keys of value
    If length of keys_list is greater than 0:
    Let new_size be length of keys_list divided by 2
    If new_size is less than 1:
    Return Some with value as dictionary containing Let shrunk_dict be dictionary containing
    For i from 0 to (new_size - 1):
    Let key be keys_list[i]
    Set shrunk_dict at key key to value[key] Return Some with value as shrunk_dict Return None

Note: Distribution Analysis and Quality Assessment
Process called "initialize_distribution_analysis" that takes property as PropertyTest returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize tracking for distribution quality analysis
    Return dictionary containing:
    "generated_types" as dictionary containing,
    "value_samples" as list containing,
    "generator_usage" as dictionary containing,
    "constraint_violations" as 0,
    "unique_values" as Collections.create_set,
    "start_time" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "finalize_distribution_analysis" that takes tracker as Dictionary[String, Any] returns DistributionAnalysis:
    Note: Analyze distribution quality from collected data
    Let generated_types be tracker["generated_types"]
    Let value_samples be tracker["value_samples"]
    Let unique_values_count be Collections.size with set as tracker["unique_values"] Let value_ranges be calculate_value_ranges with samples as value_samples
    Let distribution_quality be assess_distribution_quality with tracker as tracker
    Let coverage_stats be calculate_coverage_statistics with tracker as tracker
    Let bias_detection be detect_distribution_bias with tracker as tracker Return DistributionAnalysis with:
    generated_types as generated_types
    value_ranges as value_ranges
    distribution_quality as distribution_quality
    coverage_statistics as coverage_stats
    bias_detection as bias_detection
    metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_completed_at" as get_current_timestamp, "unique_values" as unique_values_count

Note: Utility Functions for Property Testing
Process called "create_default_generators" returns Dictionary[String, Generator]:
    Note: Create standard set of generators for common types
    Let generators be dictionary containing Set generators at key "integer" to create_integer_generator with min_value as -100 and max_value as 100
    Set generators at key "string" to create_string_generator with min_length as 0 and max_length as 20
    Set generators at key "boolean" to create_boolean_generator
    Set generators at key "float" to create_float_generator with min_value as -100.0 and max_value as 100.0 Return generators

Process called "create_default_shrinking_strategies" returns Dictionary[String, ShrinkingStrategy]:
    Note: Create standard set of shrinking strategies
    Let strategies be dictionary containing Let integer_strategy be ShrinkingStrategy with:
    strategy_name as "integer_shrink"
    applicable_types as list containing "integer"
    shrink_function as "shrink_integer_value"
    effectiveness_score as 1.0
    application_count as 0
    successful_shrinks as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Set strategies at key "integer" to integer_strategy Let string_strategy be ShrinkingStrategy with:
    strategy_name as "string_shrink"
    applicable_types as list containing "string"
    shrink_function as "shrink_string_value"
    effectiveness_score as 1.0
    application_count as 0
    successful_shrinks as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Set strategies at key "string" to string_strategy Return strategies

Process called "create_boolean_generator" returns Generator:
    Note: Create generator for boolean values
    Return Generator with:
    generator_name as "boolean_generator"
    data_type as "boolean"
    generation_strategy as RandomGeneration
    constraints as list containing
    dependency_generators as list containing
    distribution_weights as dictionary containing "true" as 0.5, "false" as 0.5
    generated_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_float_generator" that takes min_value as Float and max_value as Float returns Generator:
    Note: Create generator for floating point values
    Let range_constraint be Constraint with:
    constraint_type as "range"
    parameters as dictionary containing "min" as min_value, "max" as max_value
    validation_function as None
    error_message as "Value must be between " Format.float_to_string with value as min_value " and " Format.float_to_string with value as max_value
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Return Generator with:
    generator_name as "float_generator"
    data_type as "float"
    generation_strategy as RandomGeneration
    constraints as list containing range_constraint
    dependency_generators as list containing
    distribution_weights as dictionary containing
    generated_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing "min_value" as min_value, "max_value" as max_value

Process called "generate_random_integer" that takes min as Integer and max as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate random integer in range - simplified implementation
    If max is less than or equal to min:
    Return min
    Let range_size be max - min
    Let random_offset be (get_current_timestamp multiplied by 1000000) mod range_size
    Return min + random_offset

Process called "generate_random_string" that takes length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generate random string of specified length
    Let charset be "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789"
    Let result be ""
    For i from 1 to length:
    Let random_index be generate_random_integer with min as 0 and max as (length of charset - 1)
    Let random_char be Format.character_at_index with text as charset and index as random_index
    Set result to result random_char Return result

Process called "values_are_equal" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Deep equality comparison for values
    If actual is String and expected is String:
    Return actual is equal to expected
    Otherwise if actual is Integer and expected is Integer:
    Return actual is equal to expected
    Otherwise if actual is Boolean and expected is Boolean:
    Return actual is equal to expected
    Otherwise if actual is List and expected is List:
    If length of actual is not equal to length of expected:
    Return false
    For i from 0 to (length of actual - 1):
    If not values_are_equal with actual as actual[i] and expected as expected[i]:
    Return false
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Process called "get_value_type" that takes value as Any returns String:
    Note: Determine the type of a value
    If value is Integer:
    Return "integer"
    Otherwise if value is String:
    Return "string"
    Otherwise if value is Boolean:
    Return "boolean"
    Otherwise if value is Float:
    Return "float"
    Otherwise if value is List:
    Return "list"
    Otherwise if value is Dictionary:
    Return "dictionary"
    Otherwise:
    Return "unknown"

Process called "calculate_complexity_score" that takes value as Any and generator as Optional[Generator] returns Float:
    Note: Calculate complexity score for generated value
    Let base_complexity be 1.0 Match get_value_type with value as value:
    When "string":
    Set base_complexity to base_complexity multiplied by (1.0 + length of value divided by 10.0)
    When "list":
    Set base_complexity to base_complexity multiplied by (1.0 + length of value divided by 5.0)
    When "dictionary":
    Let keys_list be keys of value
    Set base_complexity to base_complexity multiplied by (1.0 + length of keys_list divided by 5.0)
    Otherwise:
    Set base_complexity to 1.0 Return base_complexity

Process called "get_constraint_parameter" that takes generator as Generator and constraint_type as String and parameter as String and default as Any returns Any:
    Note: Get constraint parameter with default fallback
    For each constraint in generator.constraints:
    If constraint.constraint_type is equal to constraint_type and constraint.parameters contains key parameter:
    Return constraint.parameters[parameter] Return default

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Get current timestamp - would delegate to system in production
    Return 0.0

Process called "keys" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, Any] returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract keys from dictionary
    Return list containing

Process called "call_property_function" that takes function_name as String and args as List[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Call property function with arguments - would delegate to runtime
    Try:
    Return dictionary containing:
    "success" as true,
    "result" as true,
    "output" as "",
    "execution_time" as 0.001,
    "error_message" as ""
    Catch error:
    Return dictionary containing:
    "success" as false,
    "result" as false,
    "output" as "",
    "execution_time" as 0.0,
    "error_message" as error.message